article.description: — Makuach Maluach had 22 points as New Mexico defeated Air Force 73-65 on Monday night.
article.headline: Maluach scores 22 to lead New Mexico past Air Force 73-65
article.linkText: Maluach scores 22 to lead New Mexico past Air Force 73-65
article.story: AIR FORCE ACADEMY, Colo. -- — Makuach Maluach had 22 points as New Mexico defeated Air Force 73-65 on Monday night. Valdir Manuel had 14 points for New Mexico (6-13, 2-13 Mountain West Conference), which ended its five-game losing streak. Bayron Matos added 13 points and seven rebounds. Saquan Singleton had 5 points, 13 assists and six rebounds. A.J. Walker had 26 points for the Falcons (4-17, 2-15), who have now lost 10 games in a row. Chris Joyce added 16 points and eight rebounds. Abe Kinrade had 15 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
